org.apache.commons.rdf.simple

Class DummyRDFParserBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.commons.rdf.simple.experimental.AbstractRDFParser<DummyRDFParserBuilder>
      • org.apache.commons.rdf.simple.DummyRDFParserBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cloneable, org.apache.commons.rdf.experimental.RDFParser

    public class DummyRDFParserBuilder
extends AbstractRDFParser<DummyRDFParserBuilder>
    For test purposes - a RDFParser that inserts information about what it has been asked to parse instead of actually parsing anything.

    This always insert at least the triple equivalent to: 

        <urn:uuid:b7ac3fcc-4d86-4d28-8358-a1cd094974a6> <http://example.com/greeting> "Hello world" .
    Additional triples match the corresponding getter in AbstractRDFParser, e.g.: 
       <urn:uuid:b7ac3fcc-4d86-4d28-8358-a1cd094974a6> <http://example.com/base> <http://www.example.org/> .
   <urn:uuid:b7ac3fcc-4d86-4d28-8358-a1cd094974a6> <http://example.com/sourceFile> "/tmp/file.ttl" .
